Great to hear of success, particularly when it looks like you&#39;re 
employing a similar strategy to mine.  My plan today was to try 
monkeying with the CLASSPATH, though yesterday I started to think 
this would involve &quot;createClasspath&quot;, but it looks like 
simply &quot;classpath&quot; will work.  This will be very helpful for my work 
with Ant, after I establish a firm understanding of what&#39;s going on 
in JUnit.  Thanks!
--- In junit@yahoogroups.com, &quot;Paul Zabelin&quot; &lt;pavel_zabelin@3...&gt; 
wrote:
&gt; You can do separate compilation for test clases into separate 
&gt; directory, then use junit task with classpath pointing to both test 
&gt; classes and classes to be tested. It will still require to know the 
&gt; location of *.java files, but it can be separate folder. Here is an 
&gt; example from my build.xml, where java files are in java/test 
compiled 
&gt; to ${test.home}/junit/classes folder.
&gt; 
&gt;   &lt;target name=&quot;test&quot; depends=&quot;compile&quot;
&gt;    description=&quot;Unit Test DAO (Database Access Objects) Java 
sources&quot;&gt;
&gt; 
&gt;     &lt;mkdir    dir=&quot;${test.home}/junit/classes&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 
&gt;     &lt;javac srcdir=&quot;java/test&quot;
&gt;           destdir=&quot;${test.home}/junit/classes&quot;
&gt;            debug=&quot;yes&quot;
&gt;      deprecation=&quot;yes&quot;
&gt;        classpath=&quot;${build.home}/WEB-INF/classes&quot;
&gt;         excludes=&quot;**/CoverageTest.java&quot;&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/javac&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; 	&lt;junit printsummary=&quot;no&quot; 
&gt; haltonfailure=&quot;${test.haltonfailure}&quot;&gt;
&gt; 	  &lt;classpath&gt;
&gt; 	    &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${test.home}/junit/classes&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 	    &lt;pathelement location=&quot;${build.home}/WEB-INF/classes&quot;/&gt;
&gt;         &lt;pathelement 
&gt; location=&quot;${catalina.home}/common/lib/classes12.jar&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 	  &lt;/classpath&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; 	  &lt;formatter type=&quot;xml&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; 	  &lt;batchtest fork=&quot;no&quot; todir=&quot;${test.home}/junit&quot;&gt;
&gt; 	    &lt;fileset dir=&quot;java/test&quot;&gt;
&gt; 	      &lt;include name=&quot;**/*Test.java&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 	      &lt;exclude name=&quot;**/CoverageTest.java&quot;/&gt;
&gt; 	    &lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt; 	  &lt;/batchtest&gt;
&gt; 	&lt;/junit&gt;
&gt; 
&gt;     &lt;junitreport todir=&quot;${test.home}/junit&quot;&gt;
&gt;       &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${test.home}/junit&quot;&gt;
&gt;         &lt;include name=&quot;TEST-*.xml&quot;/&gt;
&gt;       &lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt;       &lt;report format=&quot;frames&quot; todir=&quot;${test.home}/junit&quot;/&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/junitreport&gt;
&gt; 
&gt;     &lt;!-- Start web browser and open report for Windows 2000 
&gt; covinience --&gt;
&gt;     &lt;exec executable=&quot;cmd&quot; os=&quot;Windows 2000&quot;&gt;
&gt;         &lt;arg value=&quot;/c&quot;/&gt;
&gt;         &lt;arg file=&quot;${test.home}/junit/index.html&quot;/&gt;
&gt;     &lt;/exec&gt;
&gt;   &lt;/target&gt;
